Czech Stocks: Erste, New World Resources Move in Prague Trading

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-10-07T14:54:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-07/czech-stocks-cez-new-world-resources-move-in-prague-trading.html
The  Czech Republic ’s PX equity index
advanced for a third day, gaining 1.4 percent to 950.1 at its
4:28 p.m. close in Prague, the highest in three weeks.  The following were among the most active stocks on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (EBS)   advanced 4.6 percent to 512.8
koruna, a three-week high. The Austrian lender was upgraded to
“buy” from “hold” at Societe Generale SA.  New World Resources Plc (NWR CP), the biggest coking-coal
producer in the Czech Republic, increased 4.5 percent to 136.9
koruna. It had its biggest three-day rally in 1 1/2 years of
12.3 percent.  Europe ’s benchmark coal futures contracts rose for
a third day to $120.1 a metric ton.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in  Prague  at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  